costumes and theatrical performances. Bars scattered throughout the property serve local and international beverages, including premium spirits, craft cocktails, draft beer, and non-alcoholic refreshments available from morning until late evening.<\\/p><h3>Entertainment and Activities for All Ages<\\/h3><p>What distinguishes the Magic Excalibur Hotel from competing Benidorm properties is its comprehensive entertainment programming designed for multi-generational appeal. The animation team orchestrates daily activities ranging from water aerobics and beach volleyball to arts and crafts sessions for younger guests. Evening shows transform the main theater into a venue for live music, flamenco performances, magic acts, and comedy routines that keep guests entertained without leaving the property.<\\/p><p>The centerpiece Excalibur Medieval Tournament operates as a separately ticketed dinner show, though hotel guests receive preferential booking and discounted rates. This spectacular evening features skilled knights engaged in authentic jousting competitions, sword fighting demonstrations, and equestrian displays that thrill audiences while serving a four-course medieval feast. Children\'s clubs provide supervised activities for ages four to twelve, granting parents precious relaxation time at the spa or poolside while kids engage in age-appropriate games and entertainment.<\\/p><h3>Location Benefits and Nearby Attractions in Benidorm<\\/h3><p>Situated directly on Poniente Beach, the Magic Excalibur Hotel grants immediate access to Benidorm\'s famous golden sands and warm Mediterranean waters. The location offers calmer beach conditions compared to the bustling Levante Beach area, attracting families seeking safer swimming environments for children. A scenic coastal promenade extends along the beachfront, perfect for sunset strolls, jogging, or cycling adventures exploring Benidorm\'s extensive seafront.<\\/p><p>The hotel\'s positioning places guests within easy reach of